$ /etc/passwd

→ Linux/user[User] account information: each line represents a user and is colon-separated with the following fields:

1) username,
-
2) → development/security/password[password] (nowadays usually x, see `→ Linux/fhs/etc/shadow`)
-
3) user id
-
4) default → Linux/group[group] id (See `→ Linux/fhs/etc/group`)
-
5) gecos,
-
6) The user's → Linux/home-directory,
-
7) The name of the program to be run when a user logs in, usually a → Linux/shell.

In order to prohibit a user from logging in, the programm to be launched (7) might be set to `/bin/false`

The file should be edited with `→ Linux/shell/commands/vipw`.

sa:
 `→ Linux/fhs/etc/group`

  → Linux/shell/commands[Shell commands] `→ Linux/shell/commands/chpasswd`, `→ Linux/shell/commands/passwd` and
 `→ Linux/shell/commands/getent`

  → Linux/security/password

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/doc/base-passwd/users-and-groups_txt_gz`
